I find its a much better snare than bonds..<br>
And YES I've snared myself due to lag or misjudging<br>
distance.<br>
<br>
My little trick when I'm kiting the baddies in Skyfire:<br>
<br>
Once in awhile Atol's is resisted or fizzles on me..<br>
I make sure the mob is following me..then I run out<br>
of range ..over a hill or around a corner. I make sure<br>
the mob is out of range..by clicking on my hotkeyed<br>
junky little temperate flux staff. That helps me gauge<br>
how far away the mob is. Gives me enough time<br>
to turn around and cast again. I've only ever seen it<br>
once where Atol's was resisted THREE times..heh<br>
thought I was a goner. But, with Atol's and Fetter<br>
I managed to regain control, med a bit..and run the <br>
mob around til I had nuked it to death. <br>
<br>
Its rare that I snare myself now..sometimes happens<br>
in a group situation when someone else is bringing<br>
in the pull..and it gets too close to me due to lag.<br>
<br>
I think Atol's is great..haven't used bonds of force<br>
since I discovered our level 51 ae snare. Oh by the<br>
way that spell..and Plain sight ..both dropped for me<br>
in Skyfire. Lots of spells drop off random mobs..have<br>
found them on lowly skyashe drakes and bottomless<br>
gnawers.<br>
